With this issue of The Reporter we lease
publication. This issue does not include our normal news coverage and the staff will not put out
a announcement issue as previously planned. We
find it intolerable to continue our service to an
academic community which makes a spam of student publications’ autonomy. If one publication
can be blanketly centered — in this case the 1966
textbook ~ then all are in grave danger.
The cancellation of the textbook is the latest
and most serious miscarriage of proper publications procedure. All regard for rule and reason
was ignored when:
l.) A collegesponsored book was received
by the college for review without the known
edge of the student editor.
2.) The book was cancelled due to what
the college counsel and President Glenn suggest have turned fabulous material though
none of it has of yet been substantially
3,) Cancellation of the book came before
