4.) The college’s Student Publications
Committee — of which the duties are (according to facility committee bylaws) “to function
as Publisher” of the college textbook, among
other publications, and ”to exercise general
supervision of all student publications" —was instantly superseded in power by administrative victim.
5.) When the cancellation of the book was
appeared the issue was placed back in the
hands of the Committee in the form of a proposal which called for Committee review and
editing of the book “for tone and balance” in
the absence of the editor. The Committee
